performances.description: Jerry sings this one with near desperation; from Truckin into the Other One with a sick jam this show just keeps on giving...
coming off truckin', this jam leads into an amazing Phil solo and then almost 12 minutes of the most ethereal sound .... sublime ....
One of the best mellow blues versions...killer noodles from Jerry

performances.venue: Iowa State Fairgrounds Des Moines, IA
performances.description: The Truckin is good but the gem is the NFBM jam that follows.
Pretty hot stuff. See Road Trips 4.3
A seamless sweet groove - into a very cool TOO. This show doesn't get enough love - all Summer '74 is hot, but this is a real corker.
These Dec. shows are just great cowboy fun.

performances.venue: Cameron Indoor Stadium, Duke U Durham, NC
performances.description: Fully jammed out vocal version in underrated jam from late '73...probably the peak period for NFBM...
This one has more of an Other One-ish feel than most...they seem like they're pushing for it but end up going in a completely different direction
Off the rails, intense blues jamming.
first/only version with lyrics since like 85, good stuff

performances.venue: Indianapolis State Fair Coliseum Indianapolis, IN
performances.description: Killer Nobody's jam in which Jerry apparently breaks a string, but Keith steps up very nicely. Some subtle Other One teases towards the end of one.

performances.venue: Barton Hall - Cornell University Ithaca, NY
performances.description: First one in 2 years and then not played for another 4.  Nice bust out.
Uptempo, funky and different.
Rare, rootsy and spare reading. The one in '79 when Jer's mic blew had more torque.
Bob + Jer CRUSH this. If you grew up with auds you'll dig it- forget vocals Blind Jerry's mic is blown after the 1st line.
First version in a few years.  Totally cool version out of Truckin...super funky licks by everyone.  Must listen!
More than half of this NFA is actually NFBM jam and a killer one at that.  At times tough to differentiate the 2 tunes.
Correct if I'm wrong but I believe that there is a NFBM jam at the end of truckin'. Even if it's not, it definitely deserves a listen.
Nobody's Fault with a fast tempo, quite different than the later versions.
First one since 1981 and next one would be 1991.  Lyrics included.  Cool verison out of space!
Super rare version of this tune at this nice show
Jam starts at around 05:45, never fully forms.  Am I crazy?  This sounds like NFBM and it continues about 3min into TOO. Very very cool stuff here.
